description: From Latin inhumatus, past participle of inhumare (“to inhume”), from in- (“in”) + humare (“to cover with earth”). See humation, and compare inhume.

verbs.description: inhumate (third-person singular simple present inhumates, present participle inhumating, simple past and past participle inhumated)

examples: Hath the inhumated / Upward aspiring, / Hath he consummated / All his desiring?
